content: What an incredible ending to this epic Platinum Jubilee weekend Following the Platinum Jubilee Pageant The Queen made a surprise appearance on the balcony of Buckingham Palace She was greeted by roars of cheering from the crowd who then sang God Save The Queen In a letter released this evening The Queen wrote When it comes to how to mark 70 years as your Queen there is no guidebook to follow It really is a first But I have been humbled and deeply touched that so many people have taken to the streets to celebrate my Platinum Jubilee While I may not have attended every event in person my heart has been with you all and I remain committed to serving you to the best of my ability supported by my family I have been inspired by the kindness joy and kinship that has been so evident in recent days and I hope this renewed sense of togetherness will be felt for many years to come I thank you most sincerely for your good wishes and for the part you have all played in these happy celebrations For her appearance The Queen wore one of Queen Victoria s Bow Brooches The set of three brooches were made in 1858 by Garrard Queen Victoria designated them Heirlooms of The Crown and they have been worn by every Queen since I recently covered these brooches in depth on April 28 Check out that post for a more detailed look at their history I hope you all have enjoyed this once in a lifetime weekend just as much as I have Congratulations Your Majesty

content: All my Love and Respect to the Ambassador of All Things Good in this World and my Brother with Last night I got to watch one of my musical hero s and best buddies Rudy Sarzo play a sold out show at the Whisky with his band Quiet Riot While Rudy is one of the most prolific musicians in all of rock history Ozzy Osbourne Whitesnake Quiet Riot Did Blue Oyster Cult and The Guess Who plus plus plus he is also simply one of the sweetest most kind and loving human beings on this planet And a dog rescuer I ve been lucky enough to spend a countless amount of time with Rudy at events dinners his concerts I have his Peavey prototype bass hanging in my museum but most of all I ve got to record dozens of songs with him and his talent as a musician is just insane He is a virtuoso like a Rembrandt a Tarantino a Federer They don t make them any better than Rudy I care about the guy so much I made a collage Quiet Riot is playing the states now go check them out and Feel The Noise while you re Banging Your Head PS On the last video He is actually lost at The Whisky while playing the show I never said he was a Road Scholar I would call I m more of a Randy Rhodes Scholar rudy

content: Today we remember President Ronald Reagan who passed away June 5 2004 from pneumonia at the age of 93 The second son of Jack and Nelle Reagan Ronald Wilson Reagan grew up in modest surroundings After graduating from college Reagan worked as a radio sports commentator He signed a contract with Warner Brothers and ended up working in the motion picture unit during World War II Reagan s first marriage was to actress Jane Wyman and they had two children Maureen and Michael Divorcing in 1948 Reagan married actress Nancy Davis and they had two children Patti and Ron As President of the Screen Actors Guild Reagan opposed Communist influence in the entertainment industry and later switched from a liberal to conservative philosophy fiercely opposed to big government Elected Governor of California in 1966 Reagan served two terms before winning the Republican Presidential nomination in 1980 the governor defeated President Jimmy Carter in a landslide to become the 40th president President Reagan came to office at a low point in American history Unemployment was at a record high and inflation was rampant After surviving an early assassination attempt the president deregulated industry and massively cut taxes along with non military spending fueling the strong economic growth of the 1980s He took a hard line against the Soviet Union denouncing it as the Evil Empire while increasing America s military capacity In 1984 voters re elected the president in a landslide While the Iran Contra scandal loomed over his second term Reagan remained immensely popular throughout his time in office leaving with a 68 approval rating in 1989 Though he planned an active retirement Reagan was diagnosed with Alzheimer s disease in 1994 He withdrew from public life and spent his final decade under the care of his family nhistory

content: Archaeopteryx is a genus of bird like dinosaurs Archaeopteryx lived in the Late Jurassic around 150 million years ago in what is now southern Germany during a time when Europe was an archipelago of islands in a shallow warm tropical sea much closer to the equator than it is now Archaeopteryx was long considered to be the beginning of the evolutionary tree of birds It has qualities that helped define what it is like to be a bird such as its long powerful front limbs However in recent years the discovery of several small feathered dinosaurs has created a mystery for paleontologists raising questions about which animals are the ancestors of modern birds and which are their relatives Archaeopteryx was roughly the size of a raven with broad wings that were rounded at the ends and a long tail compared to its body length It could reach up to 500 millimetres 20 in in body length with an estimated mass of 0 8 to 1 kilogram 1 8 to 2 2 lb Artwork by daily extinct animals facts be sure to follow you don t want to miss out on any extinct content be sure to hit the bell icon to receive notifications for whenever I post ion animals record

content: HYPERSONIC SUNDAY DARKSTARThrottle up We re leaving supersonic speeds for now and accelerate to hypersonic speed About a week after the long awaited Top Gun Maverick finally hit the theaters the Skunk Works division of Lockheed Martin released some details about the creation of the Darkstar hypersonic aircraft featured in the film The involvement of the Skunk Works in the project had already been confirmed by the CEO of Lockheed Martin James Taiclet in a post on LinkedIn after the world premiere of the film Now the company added on its website a page dedicated to Top Gun and the mysterious Darkstar Lockheed Martin Skunk Works thrives on tackling seemingly impossible work developing technologies for tomorrow s challenges before the need is even identified From creating radar evading stealth capabilities to X planes that redefine the sonic boom to many revolutionary technologies in between Skunk Works has a long tradition of quickly developing enduring innovation for when it s needed most When the Top Gun Maverick team was looking to push the envelope and stand true to Maverick s Need for Speed Skunk Works was their first call With the Skunk Works expertise in developing the fastest known aircraft combined with a passion and energy for defining the future of aerospace Darkstar s capabilities could be more than mere fiction They could be reality Full report at TheAviationist com Maverick

content: Paolo possesses a lethal combination of size strength fluidity as a ball handler masterful footwork and the vision to capitalize off the attention he draws The depth of his skillset will make him effective in a bunch of ways can let him face up in the mid post overpower guards in the low post use him as a screener who can roll pop and pass or utilize him as a DHO dribble handoff hub Not many glaring holes to poke at with Paolo s game but the two areas in question are the jumper and defense Becoming a legitimately dangerous shooter vs a decent one would open up even more playmaking avenues for him and make his midrange more effective make him an easier fit around other stars if he doesn t end up being THE guy Defensively with enough quickness to hold his own vs most guards and the size to contest shots at the rim i m not too concerned with him becoming at least solid eventually There s some things to clean up closeouts off ball lapses etc like most rookies Personally i d lean towards Paolo with the 1st pick if I were Orlando I don t think any of the top prospects clear one another so given Orlando s need for a top creator i d go with the guy who has the best chance of becoming that They have plenty of great young pieces that would fit well around a lead initiator in place but likely no true

content: There s no doubts about Jabari Smith Jr s skillset immediately translating to the league He already brings two elite attributes to the table and will fit easily alongside whoever he ends up playing with Someone with his size shooting ability and defensive versatility is bound for success in the league The question is whether he can become more than a complimentary star which will depend heavily upon his improvements as a driver and ball handler Jabari struggled to consistently score through contact he s a good athlete in the open floor but generally stiff and upright with a defender on his hip unable to get low and generate power to finish strong on drives Finding a reliable way to score inside the arc and pressure the defense is key for two reasons 1 Generating easy buckets He s quite reliant on tough pull ups and while he s good enough to live on those there will be nights those don t fall at the same clip Take Khris Middleton for example he s great but we ve seen some rough shooting nights for this reason 2 Unlocking his playmaking While hitting pull ups right in a defender s grill is extremely tough and a very useful skill it s not something that really collapses the defense If Jabari can get downhill more frequently to pressure the defense it ll open up more playmaking opportunities The ball handling ties into both A tightened handle would help him create easier looks for himself make him more comfortable on drives attacking closeouts and make it harder for defenders to make his life difficult by getting into his body He doesn t need a Kyrie package since all he needs is to get to his spot and rise up but improving here would definitely be beneficial

content: Edit It was confirmed an Su 27 of the Ukrainian Air ForceVideo of what reportedly looks like a Sukhoi Su 27 fighter jet reportedly shot down by either MANPADS or other air defense systems It s unclear to which side it belongs to at the moment as both sides have claimed the kill Yuri Kochevenko an officer of 95th Ukrainian air assault brigade says that it is in fact a Russian Su 27 according to pro TG channel although both Russia and Ukraine have their Su 27s painted in blue The Ukrainian Su 27s have pixelated pattern in blue while Russian Su 27 has a wavy pattern in blue with darker Grey shadesVideo Break down Disclamer I tried posting the video 4 times in individual slides but Instagram didnt allow me to upload it for some reason 1st slide reportedly shows the moment of impact and the aircraft engulfed with flames as it goes down to the ground Filmed by Ukrainians 2nd slide shows the aircraft going down from a different angle Also filmed by Ukrainians 3rd slide shows the smoke rising from the crash site filmed by Ukrainians 4th and 5th slides shows the Russians filming the crash site with a drone and have claimed that it is a Ukrainian air force Su 27 Note The destroyed flaps in the videos shows them painted in Russian patterns and no Ukrainian pixel pattern is visible but I could be wrong More updates in story

content: How long would it take humans to construct such megastructures What do you think Comment below your thoughts Ringworld an artificial megastructure in space consisting of a rotating ring encircling a star and having an inhabitable inner surface with gravity produced through centripetal force A Dyson sphere is a hypothetical megastructure that completely encompasses a star and captures a large percentage of its solar power output A stellar engine uses the impulse of the radiation emitted by a star to produce thrust and is also called a Shkadov thruster A topopolis is a tube like space habitat rotating to produce artificial gravity via centrifugal force on the inner surface which is extended into a loop around the local star Topopoles can be looped several times around the local star in a geometric figure known as a torus knot Sources Space com Physics org Wikipedia Follow it For More InterstingAstronomy and Physics Related Contents Like Share Comment below Your Thoughts Tag Your Friends To show thisScience Physics Astronomy Space Follow it Follow it Follow it

content: How long would it take humans to construct such megastructures What do you think Comment below your thoughts Ringworld an artificial megastructure in space consisting of a rotating ring encircling a star and having an inhabitable inner surface with gravity produced through centripetal force A Dyson sphere is a hypothetical megastructure that completely encompasses a star and captures a large percentage of its solar power output A stellar engine uses the impulse of the radiation emitted by a star to produce thrust and is also called a Shkadov thruster A topopolis is a tube like space habitat rotating to produce artificial gravity via centrifugal force on the inner surface which is extended into a loop around the local star Topopoles can be looped several times around the local star in a geometric figure known as a torus knot Sources Space com Physics org Wikipedia Follow it For More InterstingAstronomy and Physics Related Contents Like Share Comment below Your Thoughts Tag Your Friends To show thisScience Physics Astronomy Space Follow it Follow it Follow it

content: The Sunflower GalaxyMessier Object 63Dude Cherry Springs NEVER ceases to disappoint This last weekend I traveled 6 hours north to one of America s finest dark sites to meet up with some incredible astronomers for the Cherry Springs Star Party The first night we were greeted with rain until about 2 30am at which point the skies cleared to reveal the breathtaking cosmos I sprinted into action and finished configuring my gear for a weekend of imaging I managed to gather about 30 minutes of luminance data before the skies brightened up from the rising sun What a treat it was to hang out with some of the worlds finest astro enthusiasts I literally cannot wait to do it again Maybe July New moon will provide more clear skies This image was not part of my original plan however circumstances required a redirect after some clouds interrupted southern imaging However even though it was not part of the plan I m so glad I decided on this object It s been a couple years since I last imaged this and boy was I shocked to find that after only 4 hours of total integration time I could pull this much signal in Just look at that IFN shell I can t wait to share what else I have in the coming days I ll tell you all about day two in my next post Until then enjoy one of the night skies coolest galaxies M63 Gear ED127 FCD100 ASI2600mm LRGB 2 filter set EQ6 R ProZWO OAG LZWO 2x5 EFW I need a 2x7 lolASI120mm guide camera today

content: Tag the good people you know It s common and easy to complain about the bad people in our industry But what about all the good people out there A few thoughts 1 When we complain about the bad people we also push those stereotypes to the forefront and train our potential clients and the general population to expect our industry to be unskilled and unqualified 2 Good coaches fixate on the problems and the people they feel who are killing it by taking cheesy shortcuts Most of that stuff is fake anyway Good coaches feel lost and ineffective in all the noise 3 We miss the opportunity to highlight all of the good work and good people in our world Sure there are plenty of bad faith actors But there are so many skilled caring hard working exceedingly qualified fitness professionals we can showcase and share Tag those people in to share them 4 Lets put more energy into pointing out all the good people and good work in our world motivation

content: Time flies It s been a week since Nick Mason s played here in Zagreb Yesterday I saw this billboard and asked my friend dots to take a picture of me next to it before it s replaced with something less appealing But let me tell you another thing During the concert Mr Mason took the mic a couple of times and shared a word or two Btw I find that brief intermezzos quite charming they remind me of intimate club jazz concerts Among other things he said that in his career which spans for 57 years he never played in Croatia before neither with Saucers neither with Pink Floyd I know that very well of course so I tried to count how many times I saw Pink Floyd David Gilmour Roger Waters and now Nick Mason s SOS in concert and guess what the number is 20 I saw Pink Floyd three times David Gilmour five times Roger Waters eight times and Nick Mason s SOS four times I know this sounds like a competition in a way but I m pretty sure that all of you concert goers know that numbers don t really matter Here they only portray an ordinary life of a devoted Pink Floyd fan who happens to like travelling too Have a great day Floydians fan

content: Today s game of the day is Super Mario 64 for the Nintendo 64 Super Mario 64 was developed by Nintendo EAD and published by Nintendo in 1996 Super Mario 64 is a 3D platform game where your goal is to collect stars Stars are needed to progress through Princess Peach s castle to rescue Peach from Bowser A fun fact about Super Mario 64 is that it s the very first Mario game to have 3D gameplay So needless to say it was a very revolutionary Mario game and game in general Super Mario 64 was also a launch game for the N64 so this game is what made many want the console due to the appeal and how groundbreaking it was In Super Mario 64 you play inside and outside or Princess Peach s castle which is like the hub world This way it gives you some a feel of free roam where you can go anywhere you want as long as you have enough stars to unlock more doors and areas To get stars you have to play levels which are mostly found inside of paintings on the wall that you can jump inside There is a total of 120 stars in Super Mario 64 however it s not needed to collect them all All though it gives you a reason to keep playing even once you beat the game Super Mario 64 received very good review scores and with some even giving it a perfect score Nintendo Life for example gave Super Mario 64 a 10 10 Personally I d have to agree since it was such a revolutionary and groundbreaking game at the time and many still play and love it today 64 games 64games collection

content: Suppression is the holding it in the holding on the maintenance of holding it all together It s the bracing that happens before the inevitable swell of emotions The lump in your throat the tears that don t leave the tear ducts The silent scream behind a poker face It s the resistance to letting go speaking up taking up space being seen It s the fear of being too much too sad too angry of being left and rejected The disappointment It s the wanting to be noticed without the audacity to say I m here It s the shame of not enoughness underneath the too muchness Beneath the having it all together is a well of untapped grief a flood crashing against the dam It speaks to the anger that s collapsed the internal fire that s been extinguished the disenfranchised power behind the walls of everything is fine It s the inflammation of unresolved and unexpressed emotions The terror of the child within who wasn t held and the metastasized pain of holding it together ever since It you had been held maybe you wouldn t feel like you had to hold it all together Being held is also being mothered Where was mother Being held invites the body to surrender to alchemize rigidity into softness liquifying stored emotions Your body is a vessel rather than a container in need of putting a lid on it Your emotions are a conduit for connection not an expression that needs to be fought against When you trust being held you won t feel like you have to hold it all together

content: It s Tea Party time Afternoon tea was introduced in England by Anna the seventh Duchess of Bedford in the year 1840 The Duchess would become hungry around four o clock in the afternoon The evening meal in her household was served fashionably late at eight o clock thus leaving a long period of time between lunch and dinner During the late nineteenth century an afternoon tea was one of the most informal entertainments to which a fashionable lady could invite her friends and acquaintances The menu was simple as were the dress requirements and etiquette only required that a guest stay at minimum half an hour It was an easy method of entertaining and one that soon grew in both popularity and extravagance photo photos photography party partytime graphy time

content: President Joe Biden took executive action Monday to beef up U S production of solar panels and other clean energy technologies He invoked the Defense Production Act DPA in an attempt to continue pushing the U S toward clean energy Under the DPA the president has the authority to expedite and expand the production of materials and services to promote the national defense President Donald Trump used the DPA to boost the U S s defenses against COVID 19 President Biden has invoked the Defense Production Act so that the U S can take ownership of its clean energy independence For too long the nation s clean energy supply chain has been over reliant on foreign sources and adversarial nations Energy Secretary Jennifer Granholm said in a statement The administration announced that it will also pause solar tariffs for two years on solar panel imports from Southeast Asia This will help ensure the U S has what it needs for clean energy projects According to the White House press release clean energy technologies will help bring down energy costs for American families strengthen the power grid and fight the climate crisis

content: This is my post on fonts and typing quirks Please listen and understand when I say that my tone isn t angry but this is an important topic Keeping things accessible to people of all kinds is SO important TRANSCRIPTS1 Fonts Typing Quirks and InaccessibilityS2 Fonts and typing quirks are two largely used things in the system community and both come with a lot of issues when it comes to keeping communities accessible This post will go into detail on that as well as how to remain accessible S3 Typing quirks originated from Homestuck and became really popular within the system community Many people started to replace letters with numbers in their text patterns or use symbols when typing When the DSMP became more popular I also saw a lot of the ender language being used These quirks are super hard for visually impaired individuals but can also affect those who have processing issues whose first language isn t English or other ND people S4 There is also a lot of misinformation around typing quirks and a lot of people saying that they are uncontrollable That is not true Typing quirks are completely controllable The only time when they may not FEEL controllable is when they are guided by compulsions Making the choice to type in a different way is a choice not something that just comes with an alter S5 ALWAYS translate your typing quirks They ALWAYS interfere with people who use screen readers and aside from that are super hard to read Many people who I ve spoken to have said that translating typing quirks should happen before the quirk and within the same message as the quirk that way you can still use your quirk and remain accessible S6 Fonts are also commonly used in a lot of communities generally to add to the vibe aesthetic of a thing There are a ton of font generators online with so many different kinds of fonts A lot of these fonts are hard to read even if they look aesthetic anyways TRANSCRIPT CONTINUED IN COMMENTS id 1a 1b 1 system

content: SHE MADE A BLIND MAN SEE Buddy Guy John Mayer perform What Kind of Woman Is This live at Farm Aid 2005 Overdriven guitars scintilating saxophone pounding bass and drums John Mayer and still the most powerful instrument on stage was Buddy Guy s voice Buddy is an all time great and a godfather of the blues guitar It s a blessing that he s still with us today John doesnt really consider himself a blues guitar player but it s clear as day that he s got BLUES written all over his soul This is one of his best solos and that pickup switch at the start never gets old When discussing his blues playing Mayer made the surprising admission that he did not feel that he had the sufficient vocabulary of phrasing to put together longer solos or to call himself a bluesman My ear goes I will simply not tolerate a solo that s twice as long as it needs to be I heard you lose your motifs I heard you lose your lyricality I heard you lose your phrasing he said That s why I don t really consider myself a blues guitar player because my phrasing gives out after a certain period of time And I love playing blues guitar I mean it s like constant downhill skiing It s an endless water slide But the ear rules The ear is the producer of the record and the ear is the one that has to call bullshit on every other part of you as a composer and a musician and a guitar player Enjoy

content: In this exclusive and first collaboration with Obumex Nicolas Schuybroek designed a truly unique Signature Kitchen which exhales a sense of profound serenity and yet feels warm and authentic due the singular material used throughout the concept The Signature Kitchen which will premiere during Salone del Mobile 2022 in Milan will be the first contemporary kitchen design entirely finished with tin As a starting point for this design Nicolas Schuybroek rethought the block like typology of a kitchen island and transformed it into a dynamic shape resulting in carefully proportioned shifts between the sculptural blocks The design has been conceived to grant different views and perspectives around all four elevations reinforcing the concept of a kitchen island as a functional sculpture The tin cladding wrapping the entire volume offers a high level of tactility paired with softness which contrasts beautifully with the minimal geometry of the island As tin gains a unique patina the esthetics of the kitchen will beautifully evolve over the course of time resulting in each and every kitchen to be unique designweek architects

content: Due to a change in circumstances this exceptional home is back on the market New Property Time We are proud to bring to the market this exceptionally well presented 4 bedroom and 4 bathroom detached property on Kingsbury Place in the sought after village of Llwydcoed This beautiful home is finished to an extremely high standard throughout and the attention to detail is second to none Close to excellent village amenities and transport links as well as being within easy reach of major towns and cities like Cardiff Swansea and Merthyr The main living space is light and inviting and finished to a very high standard complete with a feature stair case and media wall The open plan kitchen is well designed and well appointed with a range of integrated appliances and bifolding doors opening to a large sun filled patio The separate sitting room is an excellent sized space with quiet views to the front and is finished to a high standard A large utility room and shower room are found on this floor Bedroom 2 is a very large double bedroom and bedroom 3 is another excellent sized double complete with en suite Bedroom 4 is a slightly smaller double well presented with beautiful views The family bathroom is sleek and spacious The master suite takes up the entire top floor of this beautiful home The bedroom area is quiet with outstanding views across the valley The large en suite has built in storage his and her sinks and a free standing bath The large garden is a low maintenance combination of patio and artificial lawn and gets the sun throughout the day The well planned and well landscaped garden is very private and quiet and is an excellent addition to this lovely home A remarkable home in an excellent area 485k market market

content: These volumes outline the average feed size consumed by full term healthy infants who are exclusively breastfed from birth to 6 months In EBF dyads volumes start out small and augment throughout the first month By one month intake is between 22 30 ounces per day with an average 25 ounces Generally babies who nurse feed more frequently and consume smaller volumes than those exclusively formula feeding or exclusively pumping Exclusive formula volumes are a bit higher averaging 27 32 ounces per day For those of us combo feeding it seems intake commonly falls somewhere between these ranges If you re pregnant and planning to breastfeed knowing these volumes is incredibly helpful as it can provide a reference point for feeding and help inform expectations If you re combo feeding and offering bottles knowing what average size feeds are anticipated for certain ages may help inform how you supplement If all these numbers are stressful or this doesn t look like your dance this isn t an invitation to stop doing what s working for you It s just another bit of information to throw in your pocket if it might be useful for you Have you used these volumes to help gauge your own feeding practices What does feeding look like for you

content: Hoping this post does well since it was HOT out and it took me several tries to get good photos It s a rare Deva appearance I hadn t worn this suit for proper photos in a while so I was excited to try her on again I have been using my Twitter also LividPuppy a lot lately for random photos and little notes and it has been fun I am slowly growing as an account over there but am still very tiny so I would love any follows retweets that y all don t mind giving Today I plan on drawing a bit maybe doing some fursuit making work and mostly just laying down since I m sooo tired Might game a bit too we will see I am waiting for my lovely to wake up and hopefully play some WoW with me again I literally woke up ate a special lunch to celebrate sister graduating and took suit photos then here we are now I haven t been awake for too long yet here I am trying not to fall back asleep I guess that s what I get for getting 5 hours of sleep lol That may seem like a lot to some people but this fox needs about 9 to function perfectly I am going to work on lining the mouth sewing the teeth on the costume I m making today Hoping it turns out well From what I ve experienced so far fursuit making is an absolute blast I hope everyone is having a nice day and thank you for any interaction I get on this post I know outside grassy photos of mine never do great but I think some are so pretty

content: Goma Yuzu Formerly sharing a space at The Herencia along Kim Yan Road with other F B names KURA Patisserie had recently made a move out to its very own space at 79 South Bridge Road now located along the same stretch of shophouses that one will find Thai eatery Un Yang Kor Dai which is also opposite where DAWN is situated at Taking over the shophouse that was previously occupied by Farmz KURA Patisserie has spruced up the interior by giving it a slightly more Scandinavian look the use of wooden furnishing and fittings with cushioned seats against white walls creates a look that is simple yet welcoming Having visited KURA Patisserie when they had first opened they have since expanded their selection from mostly entremets to include pastries and breads such as focaccia as well as croissants and danishes as well KURA Patisserie now also serves up a savoury bites menu which includes mains such as soups toasts and croissant sandwiches Beverages available here includes specialty coffee and tea local Kopi and Teh as well as a Citrus Honey Yuzu Soda Cold brew coffee from Narrative Coffee Stand can also be spotted in their display chiller as well Skimming through the selection of cakes which they have to offer the Goma Yuzu was one that stood out the most to us With an aesthetic that replicates that of a black rose the Goma Yuzu came with elements such as Black Sesame Baked Mochi and Yuzu Curd continuation of caption in the comments section below

content: vegan food diet_ How did you find the recipes click the link in bio food diet Get our new 100 delicious vegan recipes Cookbook including 30 day meal plans link in our bio food diet Easy Crispy Rice Dumpling for your weekend meal prep This recipe is perfect to use leftover rice or broccoli stems or other vegetables you have on hand Just chop them small sautÃ© and simply season with your favorite sauces Then you ll roll out the dumpling wrapper to make it thinner and fill it with the above mixture Pan fry until golden brown and dip in a sweet chili lime sauce This recipe is an adaptation of my Shanghai Shao Mai and sticky rice roll made from Yuba Cooking Notes Instead of using sticky rice I used sushi rice You can use other grain some lower starch grain may not stick as well so handle accordingly when wrapping them I always have some stems in the fridge for fried rice or dishes like that but you can definitely use any vegetables you have on hand Most dumpling wrappers are around 3 in diameter I simply roll it out thinner to double its size or as thin as you can without breaking it It s best to roll the dumpling wrappers in a stack instead of one by one I hope you like this crispy rice dumpling Have a great weekend Best WoonHeng éŸµé¦¨ p s Thank you to those who reached out about my IG issues and gave me suggestions I finally got in this morning and hopefully it won t happen again

content: Did you know that 75 of people give up on their latest healthy eating weight loss fitness and or diet goals within the first month The 28 Day plant based and vegan Diet Program is an effective results driven system to help you keep those pounds off 28 days is all you need to start a great habit Join Program Now food diet_ Link in BioWhat are you making today If you need ideas give these baked curry puffs a try Curry puff very similar to Samosa is a popular snack in the Southeast Asia region It also shares many similarities with Empanada Usually when something looks similar and appears in many regions and cuisines it just shows you it is a winner The yumminess of the curry potatoes inside a flaky crust is just sooo good It is best to go with pulled tea teh tarik or coffee The main ingredients for these curry puffs include potatoes sambal vegetables and puff pastry Curry puff or Karipap å’–å–±è§’ GÄ lÃ­ jiÇo is one of my favorite savory pastries growing up especially when I was in elementary school It was normally sold side by side with keropok assorted fried fritters and cost about 0 25 each I made this many times for my family as a quick snack or school lunch I hope you give them a try too Few tips I filled these curry puffs with a potato but you can use sweet potato and adjust the seasoning accordingly If you don t feel like using puff pastry you can use bread Take a slice of bread and use a rolling pin to flatten it Then fill it with the potato filling and seal the edges using a fork Brush both sides with vegan egg wash and bake or air fried until lightly golden Just grease the pan or the inner basket for a crispier texture Love the Recipe Dont Forget to Follow For Daily Amazing Content food diet_ Wishing you a great Sunday stay safe and well Best WoonHeng éŸµé¦¨ s

content: 3 people are dead and a 4th person is critically wounded after a shooting in police said All adults Around 9 30 a m Tuesday morning near the 1500 block of Maple Avenue Police gave out little information about the shooting They said they are working to identify the victims suspects and a motive Police Chief Renado Prince urged anyone who has information about any of the recent shootings to come forward If we don t have the community giving us those hits those clues those leads that we can follow up we are powerless Renado listed a dozen shootings since June 1st He said police believe two of the shootings are gang related but said the city has not seen an overall increase in gang gun violence The shooting was the second of the day and the 12th in the coastal city in the past seven days The city has had a rash of shootings in the last week including a fatal shooting on Monday a separate non fatal shooting Tuesday morning and multiple shootings last week The federal government has various definitions of mass shooting or mass killings Most agree that a minimum of three or four people must be killed within one event and in one or more locations in proximity Typically shootings that involve family members or where only rival gang members killed are excluded from the official definitions so this would be classified likely as a shooting and not mass due to its probability to be a gang shooting Follow my other accounts revival worlds todaywarsforever wars todayJoin my Telegram link in bio for up to date news and OSINT

content: P All teachers have talked of putting an end to chattering to the peripheral influence Krishnamurti Do you not see when chattering does not matter it is finished It is strange how it works I think this is the central thing which the professionals have missed Would you say from the point of view of the guru that he is concerned only with the peripheral change P No He is concerned with the central change To you there is no difference between the centre and the periphery Within the so called centre there is the first and the last step The gurus would say get rid of the peripheral chattering Krishnamurti When the sun is shining you cannot do anything about it When it is not there what are we to do Pause We do not see Pause What will man make of the statement let it chatter The fact is there is no duality and the observer is the observed at all times The noise of the periphery is the noise of the observer When the observer is not the noise is not When there is resistance the observer comes into existence Can one really see that the seer is the seeing and not accept that statement as an axiom as an interpretation But we see that the professionals have made that into a slogan Is there liberation for the man who takes drugs who takes to breathing in and out for years It may lead to a distorted mind And the man who analyses and wants to understand do you think he will find liberation So if you deny all that it is there on a silver platter It is offered Never repeat anything Never say anything you do not know which you have not lived That brings a tremendous aloneness which is pure crystal clear J Krishnamurti Dialogue 8 New Delhi 26th December 1970 The backward flowing movement Tradition and Revolution fulness

Henry Glogau came up with the idea after a study semester in Chile While working with the social inclusion NGO Techo he visited the Mejillones neighborhood where he witnessed the severe weather endured by the people He created a portable solar distiller that can provide up to 18 liters of clean drinking water Henry developed The Distiller which is based on the hydrological cycle and uses Solar desalination for distilling the water through evaporation and condensation The distiller is composed of a canopy that holds the water an interior funnel that collects the liquid and a bamboo support framework According to Henry the construction may be modified to just employ the canopy and funnel allowing it to be suspended between buildings While the main purpose of the distiller is to be able to purify water the canopy further provides shade for the community away from harsh sunlight The top layer is made from UV resistant translucent material allowing sunshine to permeate the water On the other hand the bottom layer is a heat absorbing plastic that holds the water After the water has been purified the Distiller could easily be folded up and carried back into its respective storage area To learn more visit his Youtube Channel at Henry Glogau Source Goods News Network DezeenDo you know someone who is a Sustainability Champion Share their story with us DM us or send an email to hello com Share the good news Champions

content: Get asked a lot about what I eat don t eat in the morning when doing 16 8 fasting Super simple breakfast is supplements green shake EAA powder and coconut derived MCT Then a electrolyte tablet in my water bottle to take to the gym at 1pm That s it Todays session was 1k run sub 4 201k row sub 3 30X5Felt great Got home at 2 30pm and had my first meal And yes I know that some people would regard having anything in the morning as not being proper 16 8 i m doing it purely to have an easy way to limit my calorie consumption over the whole day in a way that leaves my mornings feeling energised If I eat breakfast early it just set in play a desire to keep eating afterwards there is a time and a place for that in my training but at 100 kg it s not yet

content: Introducing Peter R and Franklin L Survivors of the neglect case that we worked on in May We approached this case with the mindset that we would help whoever didn t have a secure home We weren t planning on taking in any large animals but as soon as I walked up to the stall where Peter and Franklin had been living I looked at them and knew instantly that they were coming home with us They were living on feces mixed with matted straw that was atleast two feet high underneath them and they were covered in their own urine and feces We were told that they had been in their stall for nearly two years When it came time to load them into the trailer and bring them home the team had to use a sledgehammer to open their door I ll share this footage after the trial As they walked to the trailer we saw their testicles They had been banded a castration technique and both were necrotic and infected The hospital didn t have room for them so our vet came out first thing the next morning and treated them at the sanctuary They re still receiving care for the banding three weeks later Despite the terrible conditions they were living in and the neglect they were subjected to Peter and Franklin are the absolute sweetest boys Their names have a very sentimental special meaning which we ll share at another time We are so happy to have them here at UNH and can t wait to continue sharing their new lives with you Thank you so much to everyone who donated towards their care and made it possible for us to save three lives on that day We ll be sharing the third rescue with you this week Welcome home sweethearts Wait until you see what s in store ism

content: Gartang Gali The hundreds of years old silk route renovated into a tourist attraction in Uttarkashi District of Uttarakhand Roughly a 2 3 hour journey from Uttarkashi and half an hour from Gangotri The hike to this place is roughly 5 kms both ways from the national highway and the entry fee is Rs 150 per person No permit is required to do this hike This hike gives you some of the most surreal view of Nelong Valley and Jaad Ganga river along with steep vertical mountains and Deodar forests Do not miss this when in Uttarkashi info india of india

content: Captain America does NOT runaway Captain America Sentinel of Liberty 1 ReviewLanzing and Kelly have crafted a perfect first issue that captures exactly who Steve Rogers is and where he stands now Before diving it into any action we get to see what a quiet day looks like for Steve He takes art classes where he s become friends with three classmates goes to a Mets baseball game and even trains a young boy who s been bullied This first half of the comic is delightful Reading Steve being a regular guy is engaging and heartwarming We see who Steve truly is underneath the suit At no surprise he s very caring for anyone and everyone The creative team does a solid job in displaying what Steve thinks it means to be Captain America This will be a theme throughout the series and it s a smart approach and needs to be told I think the creative team can do it by adding a flare of both realism and comics without being too excessive with the message Carnero and Woodard deliver stellar pages While capturing who Steve is through the quiet moments by mixing a cool past and present mix we also get to see Cap s classic suit shine The design just pops right off the page with a perfect blend of old and new Pacing was top notch and the panel layout was one of the reasons The quiet moments had more basic layout while the action scenes had engaging angular panels leveling up the intensity Issue Captain America Sentinel of Liberty 1Writer Jackson Lanzing Collin KellyArtist Carmen CarneroColorist Nolan WoodardLetterer VC s Joe Caramagna Podcast is live on all platforms DM if you need reading recommendations comics sentinelofliberty

content: Impressive experiment Scientists call it the Rubber Hand Illusion What does it show and why is it important Scientists use the trick with a fake hand to explore how the mind reacts to body ownership When visual information seeing the rubber hand being stroked conflicts with tactile information feeling but not seeing one s own hand being stroked the brain trusts what it sees over what it feelsIt is fascinating how the human brain can be easily deceived The same happens with cognitive biases when we make decisions What we see think or feel does not necessarily reflect the realityVia Pascal Bornet Video credit S Nouri

content: Remember this Tullie Wollaston was the pioneer who introduced Australian opal to the world stage His book Opal The gem of the never never is a classic and first describes the discovery of seam opal at White Cliffs in 1890 by a party of kangaroo shooters and notes that stones were something quite new and exceedingly interesting with fossil shells saurian bones and strange bunches the so called pineapples of the miners which were weathered out of the hillside and strewn across the surface bleached by the sun Just look at this modern mined pineapple from 2017 incredible with not only great colour and sharp form but two joined together on matrix super rare from this small deposit Studies have shown that these crystals were once the mineral ikaite the hexahydrate of calcium carbonate forming these steep or spiky bunches of pyramidal crystals However this mineral forms in water at near freezing conditions very different from where found today However in the Cretaceous when these formed Australia was a lot further south and the cold sea conditions was perfect for their formation Although not fully understood these were later totally replaced by opal an amorphous mineral consisting of perfectly arranged silica spheres precipitated from a gel those sphere sizes are perfect to interfere with light giving us play of colour Here also we see distinct bands swirls and a layering of color with an ethereal translucency The replacement mechanism has often been discussed ikaite is very unstable and so maybe the silica gel filled the cavities of the long gone decomposed ikaite As with much beauty there is often a conundrum to resolve but no denying how awesome these are This unique piece was mined from the Naatji Nest mine at White Cliffs named from the lore that says the aboriginal people called this occurrence the rainbow serpents nest the aboriginal creator of life Love it sart

content: PILLARS OF CREATION The aptly named Pillars of Creation featured in this stunning Hubble image are part of an active star forming region within the nebula and hide newborn stars in their wispy columns M16 is approx 6 500 7 000 light years away from Earth The pillars are really REALLY BIG The pillar on the left is a little over four light years long or 40 trillion kilometers The entire complex is five light years wide Our solar system is smaller even than one of the teeny tiny finger like protrusions at the tops of the pillars The Pillars of Creation probably don t exist anymore What you re actually seeing is 7 000 years old Astronomers began to speculate that a massive star exploded somewhere around the upper left corner of the image above and therefore swept the entire structure away Photo Credit Young Joon Byun azine facts nomer physics picture x

content: The Iris Nebula 2 0 It s been a long time since I imaged the Iris Nebula This was actually taken awhile ago but I never got around to editing it It s a lot better than my first outing The Iris Nebula is a reflection nebula meaning it gets its color from nearby stars Reflection nebula like the Iris need dark skies to really capture their natural color and also because they are known to be very faint If only I captured the Iris at Cherry Springs State Park The cosmic clouds of the Iris Nebula have blossomed 1 300 light years away in the constellation Cepheus Called the Iris Nebula NGC 7023 is not the only nebula to evoke the imagery of flowers though The Iris Nebula has a wide range of colors and symmetries embedded in surrounding fields of interstellar dust Within the Iris itself dusty nebular material surrounds a hot young star The dominant color of the brighter reflection nebula is blue characteristic of dust grains reflecting starlight Infrared observations indicate that this nebula contains complex carbon molecules known as PAHs The pretty blue petals of the Iris Nebula span about six light years 3 hours and 30 minutes total ZWO ASI533MC Pro color Sky Watcher EvoStar ED80 with 0 85x Reducer Optolong L Pro Filter and iOptron CEM26 Mount Java Center NY Bortle Class 4

content: Strangest Exoplanet Ever found Even through a Gas Giant it is similar to some planets in our Solar System This exoplanet is so close to its home star WASP 127 a K Type star that it completes an orbit around it in just a little over four days and temperatures at its surface surpass 1 000 C What distinguishes WASP 127b from other planets is its density While only being 1 4 times bigger than Jupiter it s 1 5 of Jupiter s mass which makes it the least dense exoplanet ever found Do you want to see more of this Follow Credits sakkmesterke Shutterstock and facts nomer physics picture x picturesdaily facts nomer physics picture x

content: The Rho Ophiuchi cloud complex in the constellations of Ophiuchus and Scorpius This is an incredible region of the sky that includes the bright star Antares bottom the globular star cluster M4 to the right of Antares and a combination of red emission nebula blue and yellow reflection nebula and dark nebula as well Antares is a red supergiant with a mass 12 times that of the sun and if placed where the sun is it would extend past the orbit of Mars It lies 550 light years from earth and it s red color is reflected by the surrounding dust Although Messier 4 is seen close to Antares the globular cluster is about 15 times further away This is the first time I ve been able to capture this object from a darker sky I added in images taken with a filter to bring out the red emission nebula regions I would have loved more exposure time on it but 7 hours in total is what the weather allowed for I used a camera lens and Star tracker to take this image Lens Rokinon 135mm f 2 8Camera Zwo ASI2600 MC ProExposure No filter 90x 2min NBZ 130 x 2 min Gain 100Mount Star Adventurer ProGuiding ASI 120mini 30mm scopeFilter None Idas NBZSoftware ASI air DSS Pixinsight s photography photo club pics

content: BIG news to announce meet Arroway our newest engine Arroway is a 200 000 pound thrust liquid oxygen and methane staged combustion engine that will serve medium to heavy launch markets This includes current U S national security missions commercial satellite launches orbital space stations and future missions not yet conceived Notably Arroway will be one of very few commercially available engines that when clustered together can displace the Russian made RD 180 and RD 181 which are no longer available to U S launch companies Our founder and CEO Joe Laurienti had this to say Arroway is America s engine of the future Medium and heavy launch capacity is what U S launchers desperately need right now and because Ursa Major focuses solely on propulsion we re in a unique position to deliver high performing reliable and affordable engines to meet the increasing market demand just like we are doing with Hadley and Ripley We re taking orders now and planning for initial hot fire testing next year with delivery in 2025 Click the link in our bio to learn more Congratulations to our entire team for their hard work cience

content: The Titanic and Dunkirk Forgotten heroes Charles Herbert Lightoller 30 March 1874 in Chorley Lancashire England 8 December 1952 in Twickenham Middlesex was a British seaman and second officer of the Titanic He was the highest ranking officer to survive the sinking Later Lightoller served as a lieutenant in the Royal Navy during the First World War first on the Oceanic which was now on war service and whose sinking he survived near the Scottish island of Foula in September 1914 and later as commander of torpedo boats and the destroyer Garry He was twice awarded the Distinguished Service Cross including as captain of the Garry for ramming and sinking the German submarine SM UB 110 in the North Sea on 19 July 1918 At the end of the war he held the rank of Commander In the 1930s he wrote his autobiography Titanic and other ships which after teething problems enjoyed considerable success However the book was withdrawn from the market after the Marconi Company threatened to sue In the book Lightoller had been critical of the role of the radio operators on the Titanic who were not part of the ship s personnel but employed by the Marconi Company Nevertheless Lightoller did not completely turn his back on seafaring he acquired the Sundowner as his private yacht With this ship he and his son Roger took part in Operation Dynamo in 1940 during the Second World War They helped to evacuate the Allied soldiers encircled by the Germans in Dunkirk to Great Britain In the process he brings 130 British soldiers to safety Charles Lightoller succumbed to a heart condition in Twickenham in December 1952 at the age of 78 May he rest in peace

content: The universe only provides options The choices are always up to you Your choices then become probabilities consequences to help determine which options you will have in the future And so on I had to explain that before I shared something personal with you Being an introvert is my jam I work best when I m on my own but it comes with limitations A while back I found myself turning to alcohol drugs whenever I felt I needed a creative spark because I didn t have other people or ideas to be inspired by And since I m ALWAYS creating something it was easy to justify the usage Before I realized it became way too much I couldn t afford treatment so I chose to remove myself from the only relationships I still had so I wasn t a burden The point of all this is to illustrate what I mentioned in the beginning Of the options I had I made a choice to exile myself until I felt better There is no correct answer when you decide anything but you have to eat the consequences and start from there I had to reconnect with my daughter but reconnecting is better than the drama or negativity that could have infiltrated her life had I chose to ignore other hard choices Sometimes things may seem impossible but if you re blessed to see another day you can still find a way Whatever position your sun or moon is in I bid you that glorious moment

content: Have you ever seen this before I thought it s a tsunami in first look The Morning Glory Cloud is a rare meteorological phenomenon consisting of a low level atmospheric solitary wave and associated cloud occasionally observed in different locations around the world The wave often occurs as an amplitude ordered series of waves forming bands of roll clouds When can you see The Morning Glory Clouds It occurs most frequently in September October just prior to the wet season What s the best place to see The Morning Glory Clouds Similar formations have been spotted around the world but the area around Burketown in Queensland Australia is the only place in the world where the formation of Morning Glory Clouds can be predicted Tag someone who should see this Follow for more DM for credit or removal request no copyright intended All rights and credits reserved to the respective owner s via

content: How long would it take humans to construct such megastructures What do you think Comment below your thoughts Ringworld an artificial megastructure in space consisting of a rotating ring encircling a star and having an inhabitable inner surface with gravity produced through centripetal force A Dyson sphere is a hypothetical megastructure that completely encompasses a star and captures a large percentage of its solar power output A stellar engine uses the impulse of the radiation emitted by a star to produce thrust and is also called a Shkadov thruster A topopolis is a tube like space habitat rotating to produce artificial gravity via centrifugal force on the inner surface which is extended into a loop around the local star Topopoles can be looped several times around the local star in a geometric figure known as a torus knot Sources Space com Physics org Wikipedia Follow it For More InterstingAstronomy and Physics Related Contents Like Share Comment below Your Thoughts Tag Your Friends To show thisScience Physics Astronomy Space Follow it Follow it Follow it

content: A visit from Saturn What if the Saturn flew past the earth ___________________________________________________________Have you ever thought how would the giant gas planet nine times wider than our own appear to us if it were somehow closer to us than the moon Well by the time Saturn gets as close to Earth as Mars is it is brighter in the night sky than the Moon because it reflects more light When it reaches about 34 million miles from our planet people on the ground would be able to see the elongated shape of Saturn s rings and some of its moons with the unaided eye However our Moon would still look larger Within only 600 000 miles to go Saturn would take up most of the sky and awe struck people on the ground would be able to see the Earth s shadow pass over its planet and rings Saturn whips by the Earth on its way into the Sun Once it s passed us the planet s back side will be between us and the sun eclipsing it and revealing its outermost rings that would previously have been invisible due to Saturn s glare The outer rings will gradually become more visible as the eclipse unfolds However we wouldn t actually survive this visibly pleasing scenario If it happened the Earth would be destroyed by Saturn s gravity whatever you have just seen is created through CGI on the basis of data collected from NASA s Voyager 1 and 2 spacecraft as well was the more recent NASA Cassini spacecraft which have approached the planet since the 1980s The video is just for educational purpose Let s Explore ________________________________________________________ time facts exploration rings

content: Back up plan I have been losing my paddle lately Balance through our maneuvers is the focus We want to be in a good body position and have the board doing the work while the paddle is adding some assistance when needed Here I was planning to bring paddle over to my heel side to add some more leverage to the outside rail for a stronger turn but I got sloppy it bounces off board and I almost lost the paddle I was able to regain control and use it to help me push through a little turn off the top It wasn t the original plan but it worked out I feel it was possible because my rail was set and I had decent body position and balance on my board to make the adjustment needed I have shared some thoughts and a few techniques that are useful while paddling but It is equally important to maintain balance throughout our wave Something to be aware of How is your balance supcanada surf ing

content: Working in retail is hard I did it for long enough But after the 12 hour shift with no break the manager still demanding all your blood sweat and tears you just have admit defeat and smile either that or just go crazy From battling deliveries trying to get stock on the shelves the special Karen complaints stupid questions from customers and knowing that you really do deserve to be paid double triple maybe even 10 x more your hourly rate you are still part of a unique breed The retail worker assistant associate manager whatever you prefer If you ve truly had enough of being a retail slave that really does deserve so much more and want a career that you actually deserve I want to talk to you I help Retail workers who are feeling unmotivated escape the shop floor work on their mindset to relaunch themselves and feel energised again Talking to a stranger can be a bit daunting I get it but our chat is a level playing field No judgement no opinion just two people you and me who want the best for you Stop suffering yet another day take the first step shoot me a message here to find out more Let s speak soon s memes meme

content: Yesterday marked one month to the start my new full time job Which obviously meant I was majorly self reflecting all day and night I keep thinking back to the months that felt endless where I couldn t find work and I was doubting every single thing I ve achieved so far kept wondering why I wasn t worth a job yeh tbh was a tad bit dramatic but no seriously constant job rejections after PhD rejections was really difficult to process But I had to keep at it for a number of reasons other than self esteem financial stability feeling mentally stimulated etc and I am SO glad I did I am proud of myself but more than that I am incredibly grateful for my new job my role at OLLMOO and my work on my blog all of which I am enjoying so much and learning so much from but meeting all the new people is deffo the best part If you re searching for a job and are feeling frustrated just remember Job rejections have NOTHING to do with your capabilities It is more to do with things like number of applicants disorganisation issues with hiring processes funding and so much more Happy Friday

content: Confession I m one of those weirdos who loves true crime Even back before it was popular I have a few podcasts in regular rotation and one I never miss is The hosts Alaina and Ash don t mince words but you have to admit that some of the atrocities in this world might best be told with colorful language They are champions for justice and giving voices to those whose stories might not otherwise be told I started to binge true crime podcasts several seasons ago when I was just starting to dabble with flower farming and I haven t slowed down since There is a strange juxtaposition of being immersed in flowers while listening to something so dark but also a light in thinking about all of the selfless humans out there who work tirelessly for the good of humanity I like to think that beauty ultimately overcomes darkness All of this rambling to say when I was tuned into Alaina and Ash this morning they said something that resonated with me Give the little girl you a hug I m taking it a little out of context but the concept struck me That we all go through tough times and someday we can look back and give that little kid inside us a hug It made me think about parts of my childhood and how I d love to go back and give little girl Melissa a hug to tell her that everything would be more than alright one day And to give her all the flowers

content: Tuhin Das in USAREPOST com groups milkywaychasers chosen by Admin to be featured or post on Facebook com groups milkywaychasers Tag a friend who might enjoy this Milky Way image and journey From Tuhin about this image STACKED BLENDEDThe rise of milkyway galactic core over the lonely petrified tree standing in the water Assateague National Seashore Maryland USA This photo is captured and featured only this year by several photographers which many of them I follow by heart My astro buddy we shoot together several times keep forcing me to visit the location and try to replicate the scene naturally obviously He already did the research visited and scouted the location month ahead Now it was wait time for the good weather and perfect moon phase I got a call from him late afternoon on weekday and he kept saying the weather may come out good Let s try tonight I have been to this location several times this year mostly for night shooting except this particular one It s about 4 hours of driving each side to the location So we went and found the devil low level clouds Decided to wait couple of hours to check if the clouds clear up Waited in the water wet feet although weather was nice and keep shooting to check if clouds aren t in the frame Got about 20 30 minutes of window where the milkyway was lined up with the tree and there wasn t any disturbing clouds So here s the final outcome Will look forward to visit here again for a slightly different composition which was the initial plan couldn t accomplish due to clouds EXIF Camera Nikon D780Lens Nikon 14 24 f2 8Sky Exposure Focal Length 22 mmAperture F 2 8ISO 16000Shutter Speed 10 secondsForeground Exposure Focal Length 22 mmAperture F 3 2ISO 5000Shutter Speed 60 seconds photo nomy photography

content: TITANIC ARTIST SHOWCASE Nathan Fowkes is a working animation artist with screen credit on 12 feature films as well as a teacher of drawing painting color and design His notable clients include DreamWorks Disney Blue Sky Studios Paramount Animation and many others There are nods throughout Sharktale 2004 that the sharks den is the wreck of RMS Titanic However the outside and interiors of the shipwreck were based on SS Normandie a French ocean liner of the 1930s Particular examples are the scenes at the bar when Don Lino and Sykes meet for the first time and the dining room where the sitting is set Nathan is also author of the bestselling How to Draw Portraits in Charcoal and How to Paint Landscapes in Watercolor and Gouache Since 2007 Nathan has been a guest lecturer at Art Center College of Design and Laguna College of Art and Design Here RMS Titanic wreck from Sharktale 2004 Discover more at nathanfowkes com prints html memoriallighthousememorial lighthouse 2022anniversary 1912

content: So yesterday I took a trip to the Bury Transport Museum at to see it s newest exhibit the famous LNER A4 Class 60009 Union of South Africa now on public display after a long career running in preservation It s certainly a sight to see this beautiful machine in the relatively small surroundings of the transport museum surrounded by its excellent collection of cars vans bikes and buses The first thing I noticed is that she stands in stark contrast to her immaculately polished sister 4468 Mallard by still wearing the coat of dirt and soot with heat pealed paintwork after a long career of steaming the permanent way and she looks all the better for it Her exterior has been returned to how she looked to the end of her career for British Rail with the red nameplate and modern warning flashes replaced by black and the classic 1960 s style ones which I really like There s plenty of information on display about Sir Nigel Gresley the LNER and the A4 s for all those that want to find out more and the footplate is readily accessible letting you follow in the footsteps of all those fortunate enough to take hold of the regulator and sit in the comfortable drivers seat to gaze at the mix of 1930s valves and gauges peppered with the modern electronics that enabled her to run on the mainline up until very recently It s well worth a visit to the Transport Museum if you find yourself at the East Lancashire Railway or in Bury You get in free if you ve got a day river ticket or it s 5 if you re just visiting the museum I believe 60009 is on show for at least the next couple of years and it s well worth going along to see this speed machine and one of the 6 A4 s that survived the scrappers torch up close unionofsouthafrica class pacific transportmuseum geek

content: Day 54 60 In loving memory of Gimuy Cairns Naarm Melbourne Kms ran today 71 92kmTotal Kms ran so far 3 601 64kmsCurrently running in Kurnai landToday was really tough I had so little energy all day but I persevered with one foot in front of the other As my legs didn t want to get going and I felt run down I had to really focus on my reasons why I m out there Today was s 50th birthday I dug deep and did my best for you coach I was given a massive lift when and surprised me with a visit to run with me and of course they brought donuts Thanks guys Massive thank you to everyone who has donated to We have currently raised 43 470 50 of our 60 000 fundraising goal If you d like to donate please click the link in my bio Together we can help Make A Wish Australia help critically ill children achieve their number 1 wish When a wish comes true a child discovers that despite their situation anything is possible This is what my run is all about Thank you to my awesome support crew on day 54 smith77Thank you to my sponsors supporters co smith77 Paul Wheelton

content: This is a Leg Raise GAME CHANGER The old school traditional way of doing leg raises is to lay on your back and simple raise your legs up and down Sure you ll feel it a bit But you also might feel some lower back pain and lots of tension in your hip flexors instead of your abs The fix Instead of just laying down focus on lifitng your head neck and shoulders up while squeezing your abs down into the ground You ll feel an instant engagement in your abs and you ll continue to feel it as you lift your legs up and down Yeah you ll feel it your neck too That s a GOOD thing Your neck has muscles that need to be worked too At the top of the leg lift be sure to keep the abs squeezed down and bring your legs up into you as much as you can I promise this is going to take this exercise to the next level for you Give it a try and let me know if it helps you out fitness tips tips guys guys sofinstagram ed motivation motivation spo

content: Long before online dating apps people desperate back then you appeared desperate if you posted a dating ad in the paper to date posted personal ads in the newspaper The dating cliche then was I enjoy long walks on the beach Fast forward to a new generation of online dating where singles use tacky cliches like I m new to this so here goes Impress me Looking for my partner in crime My friends say I m I m not knocking online dating hey it s a great way to meet people but some of the introductions are a bit corny Anyway I m not posting a personal ad in the newspaper but dang I enjoy a good walk on the beach That liner certainly wouldn t be my introduction on a dating app but it might stir a giggle among those of a certain generation who get it But honestly there s something to be said about walking parallel to the shoreline toes slightly sinking in the wet sand the waves crashes gently on your ankles occasionally kicking up the water playfully and all the while soaking up the sun and enjoying nature s beautiful elements destinations body

content: Surely enough to put you off for life It s our final day here today What a great trip it has been I had my anxieties about 5 of us sharing a room something we ve never done before and how the kids behaviour might impact our holiday Because we co parent the older girls 50 50 we re not used to all being together for longer periods Co parenting is a tricky thing to navigate You spend half your time missing your children whilst enjoying a break and then the remaining time together you re resetting behaviours and dealing with an attack of the senses This is a weekly thing for us We make the most of our situation but it is tricky sometimes It s sad to not have them with me all the time and sometimes hard when we re all together and I m managing 3 small peoples needs It s one extreme to another So this trip has cemented future trips away like this We now know we can do it and we ve all had so much fun together The cherry on the cake for me is whilst managing my struggles with certain things I ve worked through each one of them sober I ve used my internal resources to try and glide through parenting anxieties and I ve proved to myself yet again that I can do anything Now I am just Teri and not relying on wine to cope Teri I can operate perfectly well wine free and feel a deep sense of pride and happiness for cruising through situations the best I can and not numbing them out I really feel like I have come a long way from those initial single mum days several years ago Around that time I never ever thought I d get married have another baby and achieve sobriety I felt so low and worthless back then It s nice to reflect and appreciate the growth Ok now just a day in the sun and a 9 hour journey overnight Have a lush Saturday

content: I ve been asked about this recently and I remember reading about it when at my wits end googling at 3am with my first baby It went like this if your baby falls asleep in your arms and you put them down asleep when they wake up and you aren t holding them it s like waking up on your neighbours front lawn They MUST fall asleep independently supporting them to sleep is likely the reason they are waking at night As a first time mom this made sense I was thinking okay so now I shouldn t nurse or rock to sleep because that s confusing for her Lets try putting her down awake and if I ve nailed the wake window she should just drift off Well you can guess what happened next This is such a bizarre concept so if I fall asleep on the couch and my partner brings me to my bed when I wake up it will feel like I m somewhere else No Just no This is used to push parents into non responsive methods that usually go against their instincts Now if it worked for you that s really great so no need to come at me with defensive comments I really am happy you found something that worked The difficulty is it doesn t work for most babies A baby wakes at night for 87362 reasons hungry wet cold hot scared in pain misses their parent loud noise etc It s not because you nurse rocked or bounced them to sleep Maybe they are 6 months and the longest they can go without a feed is 2 hours that s normal or maybe they are not developmentally ready to link multiple sleep cycles It s not your fault your baby is waking If you rock them to sleep and transfer to their sleep space when they wake and don t need something they will recognize the smells sounds and environment Work on having them LOVE their sleep space Play in the crib during the day hang out in the room sleep on their sheets or spill some breastmilk on them Layer in lots of sleep associations so your baby has lots of ways to fall asleep Rock and sing bounce and shush sing and sway rock sing bum pats That way when something stops working you can make changes to the patterns So remember you are amazing and so is your baby You ve got this

content: This is the best pasta I have made in a MINUTE If you visit my site you ll notice an absence of sun dried tomato recipes Why Because I always found them too tangy Fortunately I am in LOVE with these Sun Dried Tomatoes with Garlic in Olive Oil The flavor is sweet robust and works perfectly in this creamy sauce I used the trifecta of Italian flavors tonight including Dried Italian Oregano and Parmigiano and Bianchetto Truffle Cream Save this post recipe is below 1 tbsp neutral oil 1 yellow onion peeled and sliced 1 4 cup sun dried tomatoes in oil roughly chopped plus 1 teaspoon of the oil 2 tbsp butter 1 tsp dry Italian oregano 1 2 tsp crushed red pepper optional 2 cups water or vegetable stock 1 3 cup mascarpone or heavy cream 8 ounces Tagliatelle 1 tsp truffle cream optional Salt and pepper to taste Heat the oil in a wide pot over medium heat Add the onion and cook stirring regularly for 8 10 minutes until softened Season with salt and pepper Add the chopped sun dried tomatoes and 1 teaspoon tomato oil from the jar Cook 3 4 minutes more Melt the butter into the onions and tomatoes Once frothy add the oregano and crushed red pepper Cook 1 minute Season with salt and pepper Pour in the water or stock and bring to a boil Reduce heat to medium low and hard simmer until thickened about 15 minutes If the sauce reduces too quickly reduce heat to low and add a splash or two more of water Taste and season to your preferences Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil Add the pasta and cook until al dente Scoop out 1 3 cup of the pasta cooking water and set it aside Drain the pasta If using the truffle cream add it to the reserved hot pasta cooking water and stir to temper it Add the mascarpone or heavy cream to the pot of sun dried tomato sauce and bring to a boil Reduce heat to medium and add the reserved pasta cooking water with truffle cream Let the sauce bubble for 5 minutes until thickened Taste and season Add the pasta and cook for 1 2 minutes more until completely coated with the sauce Turn off the heat Divide the pasta between shallow bowls Garnish with parsley Enjoy

content: Life is what you celebrate All of it On 4th June 2022 the happiness quotient at school was at an all time high the reason being our Flag off ceremony for the silver jubilee celebration of our school Dr Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan Vidyalaya Borivali The Flag off was indeed a great way to start all the wonderful celebrations at school The programme took everyone down the memory lane of how the school started and attained laurels and glories Our Principal Ma am Mrs Manisha Arondekar shared the theme for the year Beyond the boundaries and the guiding light for all the students and teachers is Dhruv the constant pole star Our Chairman Sir Shri Vikram Patel our Financial Director Mr Giriraj Khandelwal Sir and our Founder Principal Mrs Asha Damle Ma am addressed everyone on the occasion The joy on everyone s face as our Chairman sir waved the Flag and signalled the flag off with the entire audience joining in waving the flag was a visual treat The day was a perfect start to our silver jubilee celebration so come join us as we begin the fun and excitement the whole year round Special

content: Project Name Woodchester MansionLocation Gloucestershire EnglandProject Type MansionConstruction Started 1858Construction Stalled 1870Current Residents 200 Horseshoe BatsWilliam Leigh and inexperienced architect Benjamin Bucknell began planning the Woodchester Mansion in the late 1850s and construction began in 1858 The massive gothic revival style mansion progressed slowly but steadily over the next decade Unfortunately as William Leigh s health deteriorated progress slowed and by the time Leigh passed away in 1873 construction on the mansion had stopped altogether Leigh s heirs appeared to have little interest in completing the project which began to be neglected In 1938 Leigh s granddaughters sold the incomplete home to a charitable organization who intended to turn the incomplete building into a mental health hospital These plans were canceled as WWII became everyone in Europe s main focus in the 1940s The house continued to sit vacant although remarkably despite being vacant for well over 100 years it never fell into complete disrepair A small group of locals did their best to maintain the building and grounds and in the early 1990s it was bought by a local government organization It now opens the building to the public several months out of the year Several hundred bats began living in the attic in the 1950s and have been the only permanent residents the house has ever had except for all the ghouls and poltergeists that paranormal investigators insist are living in the building too Photo Credits divento craftinvaders nationaltrustuk stroudtimes revival lovers
